<br>
Beastlords can be very good at PvP, or very weak, depending on how you deal with them.<br>
<br>
Their main strength is their pet, and they will most likely always have their pet buff up.  But, it can be easily dispelled b/c the pet buff &quot;icon&quot; is on the beastlord himself, not the pet.  So, Pumice Pumice Pumice the beastlord till you're satisfied, and at this point they will most likely be easy prey (as long as you can get off a pumice (maybe by instill doubting the pet) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
Also, MR is nice against these guys.  They will often try to blind you if they catch you off guard, which can suck.  Getting MR to 90+ will most likely take care of anything magic based spells they have.   <p>~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujondinsottovoce.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jondin Sottovoce</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/02 9:32:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beastlords and pvp</span><hr size=1> Dueled a Beastlord the other day, was a lot of fun this is what I learned.  <br>
<br>
Their pets are nasty, there is currently a bug when you charm a beastlord pet, it does not break charm its yours till he zones, which in turn creates a pet that is KOS to everyone including you as the charmer.  When the beastlord zones back his pet is still withhim as well as the bugged pet that is attacking anything that moves. Strange but it happens.<br>
<br>
Now PvP tactics for a beastlord.  Get ride of their pet, just keep dispelling them  till pet goes poof, if they are foolish enough to put the buff in the first slot they are toast before the battle begins.  Once pet is out of the way you can melee them to hell and back, poor beastlord only weapons prevented him from using too many of them class only weapons but he had such poor ac it was just a matter of meleeing while watching him bleed to death on my 27 pt ds.<br>
<br>
Weak PvP's so far as i can see, unless they find a way to keep their pet alive (i.e. insta right click items while keeping their pet icon in the last buff slot.<br>
<br>
